            142.43991088867188
          ],
          "text": "(i) Penal interest shall be levied in all cases where the bank has enjoyed 'ineligible' credit \nin its current account with Reserve Bank on account of wrong reporting / delayed reporting \nof transactions.",
          "font_info": {
            "size": 12.0,
            "name": "ArialMT",
            "flags": 0,
            "is_bold": false,
            "is_italic": false
          }
        },
        {
          "block_id": "p3_b2",
          "type": "text",
          "bbox": [
            72.00003051757812,
            153.83995056152344,
            543.3435668945312,
            280.6198425292969
          ],
          "text": "(ii) Only cash held in the custody of joint custodians and 'freely available' to them is eligible \nfor inclusion in the chest balances. Thus, cash kept outside the vault/ outside the \ncoverage of CCTV cameras/ cash kept for safe custody in sealed covers for whatever \nreasons/ in trunks/ under single lock/ unlocked/ in bins under the lock and key of any \nofficial/s other than the Joint Custodians or bearing a third lock put by any official in \naddition to the two locks of the Joint Custodians, is not eligible for being included in the \nchest balances. If such amounts are included in the chest balances, these shall be treated \nas instances of wrong reporting and shall attract penal interest at the rate specified in \nparagraph 4.",
          "font_info": {
            "size": 12.0,
            "name": "ArialMT",
            "flags": 0,
            "is_bold": false,
            "is_italic": false
          }
        },
        {
          "block_id": "p3_b3",
          "type": "text",
          "bbox": [
            72.00003051757812,
            292.01983642578125,
            543.3423461914062,
            349.85980224609375
          ],
          "text": "(iii) In all the above cases (excepting shortages in chest balances / remittances, shortages \ndue to pilferage / frauds, counterfeit banknotes detected in chest balances / remittances), \npenal interest shall be levied from the date of inclusion of 'ineligible' amounts in chest \nbalances till the exclusion of such amounts from chest balances.",
          "font_info": {
            "size": 12.0,
            "name": "ArialMT",
            "flags": 0,
            "is_bold": false,
            "is_italic": false
          }
        },
        {
          "block_id": "p3_b11",
          "type": "text",
          "bbox": [
            245.36990356445312,
            335.3825378417969,
            365.90631103515625,
            455.9189147949219
          ],
          "text": "Withdrawn",
          "font_info": {
            "size": 28.0,
            "name": "Arial",
            "flags": 0,
            "is_bold": false,
            "is_italic": false
          }
        },
        {
          "block_id": "p3_b4",
          "type": "text",
          "bbox": [
            72.00004577636719,
            361.1278076171875,
            321.3974304199219,
            378.3117980957031
          ],
          "text": "2.1.4 Penal measures for other deficiencies",
          "font_info": {
            "size": 12.0,
            "name": "Arial-BoldMT",
            "flags": 16,
            "is_bold": true,
            "is_italic": false
          }
        },
        {
          "block_id": "p3_b5",
          "type": "text",
          "bbox": [
            72.00004577636719,
            388.97979736328125,
            543.3411865234375,
            433.019775390625
          ],
          "text": "Penal measures for shortages in chest balances / remittances, shortages due to pilferage \n/ frauds, counterfeit banknotes detected in chest balances / remittances shall be taken on \nthe basis of prevailing “Scheme of Penalties”.",
          "font_info": {
            "size": 12.0,
            "name": "ArialMT",
            "flags": 0,
            "is_bold": false,
            "is_italic": false
          }
        },
        {
          "block_id": "p3_b6",
          "type": "text",
          "bbox": [
            72.00003051757812,
            444.3477783203125,
            176.01602172851562,
            461.5317687988281
          ],
          "text": "3. Levy of penalty",
          "font_info": {
            "size": 12.0,
            "name": "Arial-BoldMT",
            "flags": 16,
            "is_bold": true,
            "is_italic": false
          }
        },
        {
          "block_id": "p3_b7",
          "type": "text",
          "bbox": [
            72.00001525878906,
            472.1277770996094,
            342.696044921875,
            489.311767578125
          ],
          "text": "3.1 Reporting of soiled note remittances to RBI",
          "font_info": {
            "size": 12.0,
            "name": "Arial-BoldMT",
            "flags": 16,
            "is_bold": true,
            "is_italic": false
          }
        },
        {
          "block_id": "p3_b8",
          "type": "text",
          "bbox": [
            72.00003051757812,
            499.9797668457031,
            543.3372192382812,
            544.019775390625
          ],
          "text": "Soiled note remittances to RBI shall not be shown as withdrawal by chest(s). In case such \nremittances to RBI are wrongly reported as 'withdrawals', a penalty of ₹50,000 shall be \nlevied irrespective of the value of remittance and period of such wrong reporting.",
          "font_info": {
            "size": 12.0,
            "name": "ArialMT",
            "flags": 0,
            "is_bold": false,
            "is_italic": false
          }
        },
        {
          "block_id": "p3_b9",
          "type": "text",
          "bbox": [
            72.00006103515625,
            555.2877807617188,
            340.0560607910156,
            572.4718017578125
          ],
          "text": "3.2 Reporting of diversions in CyM – CC portal",
          "font_info": {
            "size": 12.0,
            "name": "Arial-BoldMT",
            "flags": 16,
            "is_bold": true,
            "is_italic": false
          }
        },
        {
          "block_id": "p3_b10",
          "type": "text",
          "bbox": [
            72.00006103515625,
            583.1997680664062,
            543.3387451171875,
            654.8397827148438
          ],
          "text": "All currency chest diversions (both between chests of the same bank and between chests \nof different banks) have to be reported through ‘Diversion Module’ of CyM-CC Portal. The \nCC sending the diversion should initiate the entry. The receiving CC should acknowledge \nthe same. Diversions should not be reported as deposit/withdrawal. A penalty of ₹50,000 \nshall be levied for any such wrong reporting.",
          "font_info": {
            "size": 12.0,
            "name": "ArialMT",
            "flags": 0,
            "is_bold": false,
            "is_italic": false
          }
        }
      ],
      "links": []
    },
    {
      "page_number": 4,
      "width": 612.0,
      "height": 792.0,
      "blocks": [
        {
          "block_id": "p4_b0",
          "type": "text",
          "bbox": [
            72.0,
            70.5479736328125,
            437.4360046386719,
            87.73197174072266
          ],
          "text": "3.3 Delayed reporting where currency chests had “Net Deposit”",
          "font_info": {
            "size": 12.0,
            "name": "Arial-BoldMT",
            "flags": 16,
            "is_bold": true,
            "is_italic": false
          }
        },
        {
          "block_id": "p4_b1",
          "type": "text",
          "bbox": [
            72.00003051757812,
            98.39994812011719,
            543.33984375,
            170.03988647460938
          ],
          "text": "Penal interest at the prevailing rate for delayed reporting of the instances where the \ncurrency chest had reported “net deposit” shall not be charged. However, in order to \nensure proper discipline in reporting currency chest transactions, a flat penalty of ₹50,000 \nshall be levied on the currency chests for delayed reporting, irrespective of the value of \nnet deposit.",
          "font_info": {
            "size": 12.0,
            "name": "ArialMT",
            "flags": 0,
            "is_bold": false,
            "is_italic": false
          }
        },
        {
          "block_id": "p4_b2",
          "type": "text",
          "bbox": [
            72.00006866455078,
            181.367919921875,
            210.69607543945312,
            198.55191040039062
          ],
          "text": "4. Rate of penal interest",
          "font_info": {
            "size": 12.0,
            "name": "Arial-BoldMT",
            "flags": 16,
            "is_bold": true,
            "is_italic": false
          }
        },
        {
          "block_id": "p4_b3",
          "type": "text",
          "bbox": [
            72.00007629394531,
            209.2198944091797,
            543.340087890625,
            239.45986938476562
          ],
          "text": "Penal interest shall be levied at the rate of 2% over the prevailing Bank Rate for the period \nof delayed reporting/wrong reporting/inclusion of ineligible amounts in chest balances.",
          "font_info": {
            "size": 12.0,
            "name": "ArialMT",
            "flags": 0,
            "is_bold": false,
            "is_italic": false
          }
        },
        {
          "block_id": "p4_b4",
          "type": "text",
          "bbox": [
            72.00006103515625,
            250.7279052734375,
            256.71612548828125,
            267.9118957519531
          ],
          "text": "5. Business Continuity Measure",
          "font_info": {
            "size": 12.0,
            "name": "Arial-BoldMT",
            "flags": 16,
            "is_bold": true,
            "is_italic": false
          }
        },
        {
          "block_id": "p4_b5",
          "type": "text",
          "bbox": [
            71.99998474121094,
            278.57989501953125,
            543.3410034179688,
            405.419921875
          ],
          "text": "The CyM CC portal has the capability for switching/ interchanging the user within a bank \nacross the country (user manual is attached for ready reference). If a CC is unable to \nreport daily transactions in CyM Portal due to connectivity or other technical issues in that \nparticular CC, the Back Office (BO) Administrator of the bank can map the user id of \nanother CC of that bank to the CC having connectivity issues for reporting of daily \ntransactions. On completion of the transactions the user rights shall be restored to the \noriginal CC. This functionality would help CCs in avoiding delayed reporting and \nconsequent punitive action. CC holding banks are advised to include this aspect in their \nCC Business Continuity Plan (BCP).",
          "font_info": {
            "size": 12.0,
            "name": "ArialMT",
            "flags": 0,
            "is_bold": false,
            "is_italic": false
          }
        },
        {
          "block_id": "p4_b12",
          "type": "text",
          "bbox": [
            245.36990356445312,
            335.3825378417969,
            365.90631103515625,
            455.9189147949219
          ],
          "text": "Withdrawn",
          "font_info": {
            "size": 28.0,
            "name": "Arial",
            "flags": 0,
            "is_bold": false,
            "is_italic": false
          }
        },
        {
          "block_id": "p4_b6",
          "type": "text",
          "bbox": [
            71.99996948242188,
            416.68792724609375,
            419.43597412109375,
            433.8719787597656
          ],
          "text": "6. Operational Guidelines on levy of penalties/penal interest",
          "font_info": {
            "size": 12.0,
            "name": "Arial-BoldMT",
            "flags": 16,
            "is_bold": true,
            "is_italic": false
          }
        },
        {
          "block_id": "p4_b7",
          "type": "text",
          "bbox": [
            72.0,
            443.38800048828125,
            218.01600646972656,
            460.5719909667969
          ],
          "text": "6.1 Competent Authority",
          "font_info": {
            "size": 12.0,
            "name": "Arial-BoldMT",
            "flags": 16,
            "is_bold": true,
            "is_italic": false
          }
        },
        {
          "block_id": "p4_b8",
          "type": "text",
          "bbox": [
            72.0,
            470.02801513671875,
            543.3388061523438,
            514.2000122070312
          ],
          "text": "The Competent Authority to decide on the nature of irregularity shall be the Officer-in-\nCharge of the Issue Department of the Regional Office under whose jurisdiction the \ndefaulting currency chest is located.",
          "font_info": {
            "size": 12.0,
            "name": "ArialMT",
            "flags": 0,
            "is_bold": false,
            "is_italic": false
          }
        },
        {
          "block_id": "p4_b9",
          "type": "text",
          "bbox": [
            72.00003051757812,
            517.4879760742188,
            206.0160369873047,
            534.6719970703125
          ],
          "text": "6.2 Appellate Authority",
          "font_info": {
            "size": 12.0,
            "name": "Arial-BoldMT",
            "flags": 16,
            "is_bold": true,
            "is_italic": false
          }
        },
        {
          "block_id": "p4_b10",
          "type": "text",
          "bbox": [
            72.00003051757812,
            552.1079711914062,
            543.34228515625,
            651.5400390625
          ],
          "text": "6.2.1 Given the business continuity capability provided by the CyM (see paragraph 5 \nAbove), there should ordinarily be no occasion for banks to request for reconsideration of \nthe Reserve Bank's decision. However, representations, if any, on account of genuine \ndifficulties faced by currency chests especially in hilly/remote areas and those affected by \nnatural calamities, etc., may be made to the Regional Director/Chief General \nManager/Officer-in-Charge of the Regional Office concerned through the Head / \nControlling office of the bank within a month from the date of debit.",
          "font_info": {
            "size": 12.0,
            "name": "ArialMT",
            "flags": 0,
            "is_bold": false,
            "is_italic": false
          }
        },
        {
          "block_id": "p4_b11",
          "type": "text",
          "bbox": [
            72.00006103515625,
            662.68798828125,
            543.3387451171875,
            706.9200439453125
          ],
          "text": "6.2.2 Any penalty/penal interest waiver request shall be considered, only if the application \nfor the same is made in the CC portal within the prescribed timelines. Waiver request in \nany other mode shall not be considered.",
          "font_info": {
            "size": 12.0,
            "name": "ArialMT",
            "flags": 0,
            "is_bold": false,
            "is_italic": false
          }
        }
      ],
      "links": [
        {
          "kind": 2,
          "from": [
            178.6820068359375,
            293.7869873046875,
            422.4200134277344,
            307.58599853515625
          ],
          "uri": "https://rbidocs.rbi.org.in/rdocs/content/pdfs/101MD03042023_A.pdf"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "page_number": 5,
      "width": 612.0,
      "height": 792.0,
      "blocks": [
        {
          "block_id": "p5_b0",
          "type": "text",
          "bbox": [
            72.0,
            70.427978515625,
            543.3359375,
            100.8599624633789
          ],
          "text": "6.2.3 In the case of wrong reporting representations for waiver shall not be considered. \n{cf. para 2.1.2 above}.",
          "font_info": {
            "size": 12.0,
            "name": "ArialMT",
            "flags": 0,
            "is_bold": false,
            "is_italic": false
          }
        },
        {
          "block_id": "p5_b1",
          "type": "text",
          "bbox": [
            72.00003051757812,
            112.0079345703125,
            543.341064453125,
            211.43984985351562
          ],
          "text": "6.2.4 As the intention behind the levy of penal interest/ penalty is to inculcate discipline \namong banks so as to ensure prompt/correct reporting, requests by banks for waiver of \npenal interest on grounds that delayed/wrong reporting did not result in utilization of the \nReserve Bank's funds or shortfall in the maintenance of CRR/SLR or that they were the \nresult of clerical mistakes, unintentional or arithmetical errors, first time error, \ninexperience of staff, expiry of digital certificate etc., shall not be considered as valid \ngrounds for waiver of penal interest.",
          "font_info": {
            "size": 12.0,
            "name": "ArialMT",
            "flags": 0,
            "is_bold": false,
            "is_italic": false
          }
        },
        {
          "block_id": "p5_b2",
          "type": "text",
          "bbox": [
            216.0000457763672,
            250.67991638183594,
            345.87603759765625,
            267.0599060058594
          ],
          "text": "-------------------------",
          "font_info": {
            "size": 12.0,
            "name": "ArialMT",
            "flags": 0,
            "is_bold": false,
            "is_italic": false
          }
        },
        {
          "block_id": "p5_b3",
          "type": "text",
          "bbox": [
            245.36990356445312,
            335.3825378417969,
            365.90631103515625,
            455.9189147949219
          ],
          "text": "Withdrawn",
          "font_info": {
            "size": 28.0,
            "name": "Arial",
            "flags": 0,
            "is_bold": false,
            "is_italic": false
          }
        }
      ],
